<br><br>In this article, Lewis Normoyle outlines the courses considered mandatory for care workers and how they relate to the regulatory requirements of the CQC in England.
<br> 
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-22_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-24_">What is mandatory care worker training?
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-mandatory-care-worker-training--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1678968162576.png?v=1678968166" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-mandatory-care-worker-training--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1678968162576.png?v=1678968166 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-mandatory-care-worker-training--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1678968162576_500x.png?v=1678968166 320w" width="1238" height="825" alt="What is mandatory care worker training? - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="What is mandatory care worker training? - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" style="aspect-ratio:1238 / 825" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-nVkyK eXnudJ pf-25_"/><p class="sc-jtXEFf jydWoQ pf-26_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-28_"><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/products/mandatory-training-for-care-staff-and-care-workers-skills-for-care-aligned?variant=7151096070178" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 71, 178);">Mandatory training for care workers</span></i></a> includes subjects that assist care providers in meeting legislative and regulatory requirements. Health and social care providers in England are required to provide mandatory and statutory training to their staff to comply with CQC requirements.
<br>
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-29_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-31_">What is the role of the Care Quality Commission?
</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-the-role-of-the-care-quality-commission--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1678968864981.png?v=1678968875" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-the-role-of-the-care-quality-commission--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1678968864981.png?v=1678968875 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-the-role-of-the-care-quality-commission--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1678968864981_500x.png?v=1678968875 320w" width="4000" height="2667" alt="What is the role of the Care Quality Commission? - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="What is the role of the Care Quality Commission? - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" style="aspect-ratio:4000 / 2667" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-nVkyK eXnudJ pf-32_"/><p class="sc-jtXEFf jydWoQ pf-33_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-35_">As England's independent health and social care regulator, the CQC ensures high-quality care for all service users. Providers are equipped with extensive guidance to assist them in complying with regulatory requirements.
<br><br>Health and social care providers are required to comply with the following requirements by the CQC:
<br>
</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eWfVMQ bsvuZZ pf-36_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-37_">Ensure that sufficient workers possess the necessary skills and experience to meet the needs of individuals receiving assistance.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-39_">Provide care staff with the support, training, professional development, supervision and appraisals necessary to fulfil their duties.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-41_">Support care staff in obtaining additional qualifications and providing evidence, where necessary, to the appropriate regulatory body to demonstrate compliance with professional standards.
</li></ul><p class="sc-jtXEFf jydWoQ pf-43_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-45_">Without these elements, or if social care providers fail to provide satisfactory evidence that they will continue to adhere to the regulations, the CQC can refuse registration.<br>
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-46_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-48_">Mandatory training requirements for care staff
</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/mandatory-training-requirements-for-care-staff--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1679028728291.png?v=1679028732" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/mandatory-training-requirements-for-care-staff--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1679028728291.png?v=1679028732 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/mandatory-training-requirements-for-care-staff--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1679028728291_500x.png?v=1679028732 320w" width="1440" height="960" alt="Mandatory training requirements for care staff - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Mandatory training requirements for care staff - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" style="aspect-ratio:1440 / 960" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-nVkyK eXnudJ pf-49_"/><p class="sc-jtXEFf jydWoQ pf-50_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-52_">Induction and annual refresher training are essential for health and social care workers to remain up-to-date with recommended practices and regulatory requirements.<br> 
<br>For training to be considered mandatory, the following criteria must be met:<br>
</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eWfVMQ bsvuZZ pf-53_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-54_">A statutory requirement (such as the Health and Safety at Work Act) requires it
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-56_">Training is required for all employees throughout the organisation
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-58_">It is a requirement of the CQC or the local authority.
</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-60_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-62_">Care worker mandatory training courses
</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/care-certificate-training-for-care-workers--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1679029098323.png?v=1679029108" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/care-certificate-training-for-care-workers--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1679029098323.png?v=1679029108 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/care-certificate-training-for-care-workers--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1679029098323_500x.png?v=1679029108 320w" width="3630" height="2976" alt="Care worker mandatory training courses - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Care worker mandatory training courses - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" style="aspect-ratio:3630 / 2976" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-nVkyK eXnudJ pf-63_"/><p class="sc-jtXEFf jydWoQ pf-64_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-66_">Care providers are required to conduct mandatory training on the following subjects:
<br>
</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eWfVMQ bsvuZZ pf-67_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-68_">Health and Safety at Work
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-70_">Fire Safety Awareness
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-72_">Equality, Diversity and Human Rights
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-74_">Infection Prevention and Control
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-76_">Manual Handling of Objects
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-78_">People Moving and Handling
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-80_">Food Hygiene/Food Safety Awareness 
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-82_">Safeguarding Adults at Risk
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-kTLmzF cNvxtt pf-84_">Safeguarding Children.
</li></ul><p class="sc-jtXEFf jydWoQ pf-86_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-88_">The mandatory training requirements of an organisation depend on the services it provides. All care organisations must provide their staff with health and safety awareness training, including fire safety training.<br> 
<br>Moving and handling training is mandatory, and food safety and hygiene training is required if your staff prepares or serves food. Mandatory training may include data protection/information governance and complaints handling.
<br>
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-89_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-91_">Care certificate training for care workers
